column1: #Text=Ten Sleep is a city in Wyoming .

#Text=The name " Ten Sleep " comes from American Indians who marked this location as " ten sleeps " ( or ten days ' travel ) between Fort Laramie and the government 's Indian Agency on the Stillwater River in Montana .

column1: #Text=( You can find a historical marker commemorating this south of town on WY 434 . )
#Text=Today , Ten Sleep is a common stop for tourists on their way to the Bighorn Mountains , Yellowstone National Park , or ( in the other direction ) Sturgis .
#Text=The surrounding lands also attract many hunters and fishers .
#Text=Unless you really know the local backroads well , you 'll come in on US 16 and you 'll leave that way too .
#Text=From the west , US 16 passes through Worland , the nearest " big city . "
#Text=From the east , it comes from Buffalo ( Wyoming ) across the Bighorn Mountains and through the Ten Sleep Canyon .

#Text=The adventurous might enjoy the drive from Manderson through Hyattville into Ten Sleep on Wyoming Highways 31 and 49 , where you can see a variety of farms and ranches squeezing a living out of the " badlands . "
#Text=Between Hyattville and Ten Sleep you will almost certainly have to stop at some point to wait for cattle to cross the road .
#Text=( Be aware that , should you have any car trouble or anything , it could be an hour or two before you see another car - and that 's in the daytime with good weather .
#Text=Just in case , you might consider whether you 're prepared to deal with all problems yourself ! )
#Text=You could also try to find your way in from Moneta through Lost Cabin .
#Text=If you are not familiar with the local roads , before trying this , you might want to download the area into your GPS system .
#Text=As long as you 're staying in town , you can walk .
#Text=Heck , there 's hardly even room to drive .
#Text=Exhibits focusing on pioneer life in the area .
#Text=To the east of town on US 16 , on the way to Buffalo ( Wyoming ) , the canyon is a popular destination for rock climbers and bicyclists .
#Text=You get yourself an inner tube , you go to Ten Sleep Park , you get in the Ten Sleep Creek , and ride that inner tube as long as you want .
#Text=Most locals would say that if you hit the confluence with the Nowood River , it 's time to get out and walk back to town .
#Text=Ten Sleep 's own music festival , held every summer .
#Text=Every Independence Day , you can see the finest rodeo in Washakie County just west of town ; the rodeo ground is near the RV Park .
#Text=Jackalopes galore , rock candy , touristy knickknacks , t-shirts , and the best ice cream and the only malts for literally a hundred miles in any direction .
